cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with the modeling and analysis of multi-server systems with synchronization constraints, which are common in distributed computing systems. This makes cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) the most likely category. The paper also discusses the performance of different multi-server configurations, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of max-plus server models and statistical bounds on waiting and sojourn times suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible category. The paper also contributes end-to-end delay bounds, which is related to cs.PF (Performance). Finally, the analysis of arrival and service time processes suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible category.
